pos_examples:
My goal is that in the end object_2 is on object_1
I: My current initial situation is as follows: 
There are 4 objects: object_0, object_1, object_2, object_3
Currently, object_0 is clear, object_0 is on the table, object_1 is clear, object_1 is on object_2, object_2 is on the table, object_3 is clear, object_3 is on the table, the hand is empty
You:
	Think: Object_1 is not clear because it is on object_2, and I need object_1 to be clear to stack object_2 on it. I must unstack object_1 from object_2 first.
	Instruction: unstack object object_1 from object object_2
I: I unstack object object_1 from object object_2.
You:
	Think: Now that object_1 has been unstacked, I need to put it down to free my hand so I can pick up object_2.
	Instruction: put down object object_1
I: I put down object object_1.
You:
	Think: With object_1 on the table and my hand empty, I can now pick up object_2 since it is clear and on the table.
	Instruction: pick up object object_2 from the table with an empty hand
I: I pick up object object_2 from the table with an empty hand.
You:
	Think: Now that object_2 is being held, I can stack it on object_1, which is clear and on the table, to achieve the goal of object_2 being on object_1.
	Instruction: stack object object_2 on object object_1
I: I stack object object_2 on object object_1.
You:
	Think: object_2 is on object_1
	Instruction: You are finished.
I: Great!
